Barron's Penta

Bessemer Trust
Moving from steel to silicon.


 







By

Hilary Johnson

 Biography




 




November 30, 2009


 AT BESSEMER TRUST, THEY'RE ALMOST apologetic about all the wood paneling and old-world prints in the executive suite. After all, this is a modern firm that that has expanded far beyond its original Carnegie Steel family wealth and now serves 2,000 clients, many of them entrepreneurs and others from the ranks of the newly rich. In fact, those clients contribute nearly 90% of the firm's $55 billion in assets under advisement....
	      




 


